Subject: [liste-egc] 3-year fully funded PhD position on Text Generation for
 Mental Health (Munster Technological University - Ireland and CNRS GREYC,
 France)

*** sorry for cross-postings **

Munster Technological University (http://cs.cit.ie/) and CNRS GREYC 
Laboratory (https://www.greyc.fr) invite applications for a fully funded 
3-year PhD position in Text Generation for Mental Health.

The successful candidate should hold a Master degree or equivalent in 
Data Science, Applied Mathematics or Computer Science. A strong 
background in (statistical, deep) machine learning is required as well 
as knowledge in natural language processing or/and computer vision.

The PhD will take place both in Ireland and in France, so that mid-term 
stays in each country will be planed. It might be possible to get a 
double diploma from both institutions.

The work will be developed in close collaboration with the Psychiatry 
Department of the Hospital of Caen (France).

If you are interested by this position, please send the following 
information to Mohammed Hasanuzzaman (mohammed.hasanuzzaman@cit.ie) and 
Gaël Dias (gael.dias@unicaen.fr):

- Detailed CV
- Transcripts of Bsc. and Msc. degrees
- Recommendation letters (up to 3)

Applications will be studied until the position is fullfilled or before 
31st March 2020.

For more information, you can directly contact Mohammed Hasanuzzaman 
(mohammed.hasanuzzaman@cit.ie) and Gaël Dias (gael.dias@unicaen.fr).

Best regards,

Gaël and Mohammed.


